<br>
When the client-side EQ game program crashes, or the client losses connection to the game server, the game server declares this character Link Dead.<br>
<br>
As far as the game server concerns (not the server select screen, nor chat room), the client is LD'ed and stops communicating with this client-side game program. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Even</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if there is a bug or something that the game server keeps trying to talk to the client IP, there isn't any response; the client program is NOT running. Unless your computer or operating system is manufactured to reponse to EQ data packets, the server will not get a response. Or if there is a bug that EQ game reminds in memory after exiting, or crash, which may response to the data packets, which is highly unlikely.<br>
<br>
It'll be really dump for the server (or the programmer who programed this function) to keep on sending packets to an IP for 20 mins without any sort of response, i.e. acknowledge, or ack packet.<br>
<br>
